b'[Sacred Texts](../../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../../index.htm)\n[Tagore](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)  [Previous](cm20.htm)\n[Next](cm22.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n### PAPER BOATS\n\n![](img/cboat.jpg)\n\n[Illustration: From a drawing by Surendranath Ganguli]\n\nDay by day I float my paper boats one by one down the running stream.\n\nIn big black letters I write my name on them and the name of the village where\nI live.\n\nI hope that someone in some strange land will find them and know who I am.\n\nI load my little boats with _shiuli_ flowers from our garden, and hope that\nthese blooms of the dawn will be carried safely to land in the night.\n\nI launch my paper boats and look up into the sky and see the little clouds\nsetting their white bulging sails.\n\nI know not what playmate of mine in the sky sends them down the air to race\nwith my boats!\n\nWhen night comes I bury my face in my arms and dream that my paper boats float\non and on under the midnight stars.\n\nThe fairies of sleep are sailing in them, and the lading is their baskets full\nof dreams.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: The Sailor](cm22.htm)\n\n'